# Zero-Trust AI Access Flow Diagram

Paste the code block below into any Mermaid-compatible renderer.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph USER["USER — Untrusted Zone"]
        U1[Enterprise User\nAny Location · Any Device]
    end

    subgraph VERIFY["ZERO-TRUST VERIFICATION LAYER"]
        V1{Device\nCompliant?}
        V2{MFA\nVerified?}
        V3{Role\nAuthorized?}
        V4{Risk Score\nAcceptable?}
        V5[Access Token Issued\nWith RBAC Claims]
        DENY[❌ ACCESS DENIED\nLogged to SIEM]
    end

    subgraph PEP["POLICY ENFORCEMENT POINT — AI Gateway"]
        P1{Token\nValid?}
        P2[Prompt Inspection\nInjection Detection]
        P3[Rate Limit Check\nPer User · Per Role]
        P4[DLP Filter\nInput Scan]
        P5[Request Logger\nIdentity + Context]
        BLOCK[❌ REQUEST BLOCKED\nLogged to SIEM]
    end

    subgraph RAG["RAG ENGINE — AI Processing Zone"]
        R1[Query Embedding]
        R2{RBAC Metadata\nFilter Applied?}
        R3[Vector Search\nAuthorized Docs Only]
        R4[Context Assembly\nCitation Prep]
        RDENY[❌ RETRIEVAL DENIED\nLogged to SIEM]
    end

    subgraph LLM["LLM INFERENCE — AI Processing Zone"]
        L1[System Prompt\nImmutable · Version Controlled]
        L2[LLM Endpoint\nPrivate · Governed]
        L3[Output Validation\nDLP · Anomaly · Quality]
    end

    subgraph LOG["CONTINUOUS VERIFICATION — AI-MGMT Zone"]
        O1[Structured Log\nEvery Event]
        O2[SIEM\nCorrelation · Alerting]
        O3[Risk Score Engine\nBehavioral Analytics]
    end

    U1 -->|Access Request| V1
    V1 -->|No| DENY
    V1 -->|Yes| V2
    V2 -->|No| DENY
    V2 -->|Yes| V3
    V3 -->|No| DENY
    V3 -->|Yes| V4
    V4 -->|No| DENY
    V4 -->|Yes| V5

    V5 -->|Token + Query| P1
    P1 -->|Invalid| BLOCK
    P1 -->|Valid| P2
    P2 -->|Injection Detected| BLOCK
    P2 -->|Clean| P3
    P3 -->|Limit Exceeded| BLOCK
    P3 -->|Within Limit| P4
    P4 -->|Sensitive Data| BLOCK
    P4 -->|Clean| P5
    P5 -->|Validated Request| R1

    R1 --> R2
    R2 -->|Filter Missing| RDENY
    R2 -->|Filter Applied| R3
    R3 -->|Authorized Chunks| R4
    R4 -->|Context + Query| L1

    L1 --> L2
    L2 -->|Response| L3
    L3 -->|Validated Response + Citations| U1

    DENY -->|Log Event| O1
    BLOCK -->|Log Event| O1
    RDENY -->|Log Event| O1
    P5 -->|Request Log| O1
    R4 -->|Retrieval Log| O1
    L3 -->|Response Log| O1
    O1 --> O2
    O2 --> O3
    O3 -->|Risk Score Update| V4
```

> **Diagram Notes:**
> - Every denial point (❌) generates a SIEM log entry
> - Risk score engine continuously updates user risk profile based on behavior
> - RBAC metadata filter is applied as pre-filter — not post-retrieval
> - Token validation occurs on EVERY request — not just session establishment
> - Output validation is the final Zero-Trust checkpoint before response delivery